    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to map a 5′×1.5′ strip of the nearby spiral galaxy NGC628 in 12CO(1−0) emission. This strip will provide coverage of all significant galactic environments, including the galactic centre, the arms and inter-arm regions, and the metal-poor outskirts. NGC628 is the ideal candidate for such a map, as it was the target of the highest quality spectroscopic metallicity map, with a source-plane resolution of ∼ 100pc. Our proposed resolution, 2′′ beam FWHM, is a factor of ~10 improvement over existing CO maps of NGC628, and will bring the angular resolution of the molecular gas maps in line with the optical, IR, and metallically data, allowing for a wide range of detailed follow-up studies. In particular, we propose to explore the correlation between metallicity and molecular gas mass in the context of the recently-discovered `Fundamental Metallicity Relation’.</prp:abstract>
